      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of three letters from T.S. Eliot
         concerning the ill health of his wife, Vivien.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <dsc type="combined">
         <head>Contents List</head>
         <c01 level="item" id="d1e177">
            <did>
               <unittitle>T. S. Eliot to "Magaret" 
               <unitdate>October 1, 1922</unitdate>
               </unittitle>
               <physdesc>TLS, 1 p.</physdesc>
            </did>
            <scopecontent>
               <p>This letter is from T. S. Eliot, Clarence Gate
               Gardens, to "Margaret," regarding the ill health of his
               wife, Vivien.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c01>
         <c01 level="item" id="d1e188">
            <did>
               <unittitle>T. S. Eliot to "Margaret" 
               <unitdate>September 28, 1925</unitdate>
               </unittitle>
               <physdesc>ALS, 2 p. on 1 l.</physdesc>
            </did>
            <scopecontent>
               <p>This letter is from T. S. Eliot, Clarence Gate
               Gardens, to "Margaret," concerning his wife, Vivien,
               being stricken with lymphatic neuralgia and his own
               problems with his teeth.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c01>
         <c01 level="item" id="d1e199">
            <did>
               <unittitle>T. S. Eliot to "Margaret" 
               <unitdate>n.d. [September 1925]</unitdate>
               </unittitle>
               <physdesc>ALS, 2 p. on 2 l.</physdesc>
            </did>
            <scopecontent>
               <p>This letter is from T. S. Eliot, Clarence Gate
               Gardens, to "Margaret," concerning the physical
               breakdown of his wife, Vivien, and surgery on his
               teeth.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c01>
      </dsc>
